  abstract = {In summary, extreme individuals differences in threat and incentive system reactivity (used to conceptualize psychopathological groups and undergraduate analogs) specifically predicted reactions to pertinent stimuli. These results highlight the usefulness of exploring personality and psychopathology research questions using the concepts of incentive and threat motivation, as well as using psychophysiological techniques.},
